# memory — CONTEXT.md

The project's **durable, version-controlled memory** — the distilled record that travels with the repo.
Upstream: root `CLAUDE.md`. Downstream: read at session start (alongside native auto-memory).

> Layer 2 — for AI use. Read when working in `memory/`. Last updated: {{YYYY-MM-DD}}

## What to Load
| Task | Load | Skip |
|------|------|------|
| Resume / regain context | `primer.md` | the rest |
| Why a past choice was made | `decisions.md` → `../planning/decisions/` | primer, lessons |
| How this project wants work done | `lessons.md` | primer, decisions |
| Audit what's shipped | `completed-tasks.md` | (read rarely) |

## Folder Structure
```
memory/
├── CONTEXT.md          — this file
├── primer.md           — current-state snapshot for resume
├── decisions.md        — curated index → ../planning/decisions/
├── lessons.md          — project-specific lessons (distilled from native feedback)
└── completed-tasks.md  — done archive (✅; read at wrap/audit)
```

## The Process
This is the **durable half** of the project's memory (VAN-CLIEF §9 hybrid). The platform's **native
auto-memory** is the auto-capture / working buffer; **`/wrap` distills** its durable bits up into here each
session, and **`/groom` consolidates** across all layers (native · project · global · rules) periodically.
Keep these files lean — they are the distilled, version-controlled *subset*, NOT a copy of every native note.

## What NOT to Do
- Never duplicate native auto-memory wholesale here — promote only the durable, worth-keeping bits.
- Never let `primer.md` grow a changelog — it's a thin current-state snapshot (history → decisions/completed-tasks).
- Never make memory the source of truth — strategy/specs live in their workspaces + `planning/`; memory points.
- Never store secrets here — env vars / keychain only.
